name: clip-training-template
description: Improve smart image search on your dataset by fine-tuning CLIP

variables.name: Dataset with captions
variables.description: Dataset containing images with the captions as the item description. Can also be prompt item dataset, with image as the prompt, and the caption as the free-text annotation.

variables.name: Base CLIP model
variables.description: Base CLIP model to clone and train off of. Can be the pre-trained foundational model, or a fine-tuned version in an active learning pipeline.

variables.name: Newest CLIP model
variables.description: Model ID for the newly trained CLIP model. On the first run, enter the base model ID as a placeholder.

variables.name: Model config
variables.description: Configurations for the new fine-tuned model. Can be an empty dict to keep original configs, or will update existing model configs with fields from this dict.
